The paper focuses on analyzing existing detection approaches for their generalization ability in the context of multispectral person detection. This involves using machine learning algorithms and deep convolutional neural networks (DCNNs) to detect humans in images that consist of multiple spectral bands. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning and DCNNs, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also evaluates the performance of the detection model, which could place it in cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
